---
import LegalPage from '../../layouts/LegalPage.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  subtitle="KickWiz Privacy Policy — how we handle data, what we do not collect, and how subscription access works."
  lastUpdated="18 April 2026"
>
  <h2>1. Overview</h2>
  <p>
    KickWiz ("we", "our", "the App") is published by Nano Synapsys. This Privacy Policy explains what data
    the App handles, how access is granted, and your rights. It complies with the Apple App Store guidelines,
    the Australian Privacy Act 1988, and applicable data protection regulations.
  </p>

  <h2>2. No Account, No Personal Information</h2>
  <p>
    KickWiz does not require an account, sign-in, or personal information to use. There is no Sign in with
    Apple, no email and password login, no third-party login, and no sign-up flow of any kind. You can install
    the App and start using it immediately — access is granted automatically as soon as your subscription
    (or free trial) is active.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
  <p>The App does not collect, store, or transmit any of the following:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any other contact details</li>
    <li>Apple ID, anonymised Apple identifier, private relay email, or any third-party login identifier</li>
    <li>Location, contacts, photos, microphone, camera, or motion data</li>
    <li>Browsing history or device fingerprints</li>
    <li>Advertising identifiers — the App contains no advertising SDKs</li>
    <li>Health, fitness, or financial information</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. The Only Data Class We Declare: Purchase History</h2>
  <p>
    The single data class declared in the App Store privacy manifest is <strong>Purchase History</strong> —
    specifically, the active or inactive state of your KickWiz subscription as reported by Apple's StoreKit.
  </p>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Linked to Identity</th><th>Used for Tracking</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Subscription state</strong> (Purchase History)</td>
          <td>Grant access to App features</td>
          <td>No</td>
          <td>No</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p>
    Subscription state is read on-demand from Apple StoreKit
    (<code>Transaction.currentEntitlements</code>). It is not stored on any KickWiz server. New subscribers
    receive a 5-day free trial; after the trial, the subscription auto-renews monthly unless cancelled.
    Apple — not KickWiz — manages your payment information, billing, family sharing, and refund processing.
    We never see your credit card details or Apple ID.
  </p>

  <h2>5. AI Analysis (Anthropic Claude API)</h2>
  <p>
    For active subscribers, KickWiz uses Anthropic's Claude API to generate match analysis. The data sent
    to the Claude API is strictly public match data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Team statistics and form</li>
    <li>Player performance metrics</li>
    <li>Historical fixture results</li>
    <li>Venue and conditions data</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    No personally identifiable information is included in any request. Because the App holds no personal
    information about you, there is no personal data to send. Anthropic processes API inputs under its
    Usage Policy and <strong>does not use API inputs to train its models</strong>. AI-generated content is
    clearly labelled within the App as "Deep AI Analysis."
  </p>

  <h2>6. AFL Data Sources</h2>
  <p>
    Match, fixture, ladder, and player data is sourced from the public Squiggle API and AFL.com.au. These
    are read-only requests for public information; no data about you is sent to either source.
  </p>

  <h2>7. On-Device Storage</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cached match data</strong>: Public AFL data and generated analyses are cached on your device only (SwiftData) so the App is fast and works offline.</li>
    <li><strong>Preferences</strong>: App preferences are stored in UserDefaults on your device.</li>
    <li><strong>Encryption</strong>: All network communication uses HTTPS/TLS.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    None of this on-device data is synced to a KickWiz server, and all of it is removed when you delete
    the App.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Data Shared</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Apple (StoreKit)</strong></td><td>Subscription transactions</td><td>Payment processing &amp; access entitlement</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Anthropic Claude API</strong></td><td>Public match data only (no PII)</td><td>AI match analysis</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Squiggle API</strong></td><td>None (read-only)</td><td>AFL match data source</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>AFL.com.au</strong></td><td>None (read-only)</td><td>AFL match data source</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p>
    We do not sell, rent, or share data with third parties for marketing or advertising purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Because KickWiz collects no personal information, there is no personal data for us to provide,
    correct, or delete on your behalf. To manage your relationship with the App:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Delete all local data</strong>: Uninstall the App. All cached data is removed with it.</li>
    <li><strong>Manage your subscription</strong>: Settings &gt; Apple ID &gt; Subscriptions on your device.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact us</strong>: For any questions about this policy, email <a href="mailto:support@nano-synapsys.com">support@nano-synapsys.com</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    KickWiz is rated 17+ and is not intended for children under 17. As the App collects no personal
    information from anyone, this is enforced by design.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. The
    "Last Updated" date at the top indicates the latest revision. Continued use of the App after changes
    constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Apple Privacy Manifest</h2>
  <p>The App includes a Privacy Manifest (<code>PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy</code>) declaring:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tracking</strong>: No tracking of users across apps or websites.</li>
    <li><strong>Collected Data</strong>: Purchase History only — subscription active/inactive state.</li>
    <li><strong>Required Reason APIs</strong>: UserDefaults (CA92.1 — app functionality).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy inquiries:<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:support@nano-synapsys.com">support@nano-synapsys.com</a>
  </p>
</LegalPage>
